The `VirtualDOM` class implements a minimal virtual DOM system that builds and updates the browser DOM from JavaScript objects representing UI nodes. Its core logic includes:  
1) `createElement` – normalizes children into virtual node structures with TEXT nodes for primitive values;  
2) `render` – mounts or patches a virtual node by creating DOM elements, applying attributes/events, and recursively rendering children;  
3) `diff` – performs a keyed diff between old and new virtual trees to minimize DOM mutations: it removes missing nodes, appends new ones, replaces mismatched types, updates text content when unchanged, and recursively reconciles child lists.
